trend_summary: Across the sequence, built-up cover steadily expands: new housing tracts fill former fields, white-roof industrial blocks spread in the southeast, and fresh arterial roads stitch areas together. While scattered parks appear, peripheral forests and farmland contract. The landscape evolves into a clearly suburban, medium-density fabric.
notable_changes: Southeastern industrial estate enlarges markedly, adding many new warehouses.
Vacant northern and western parcels converted into curvilinear residential subdivisions.
Primary east-west highway widened and given additional interchanges and feeder roads.
